Download the weather data from the constructed URL

Source: R/weathervane.R
download_data.Rd

Return a data frame containing the SILO weather dataset, complete with prettied column names, from the given download URL.

download_data(url)

Arguments

url

A character string containing the download URL

Value

A data.frame containing the specified weather data

See also

download_url() to generate the requisite URLs.

Examples

weathervane:::download_data(
  weathervane:::download_url(
    -34.9, 138.6, '2020-01-01', '2020-12-31', c('rainfall')
  )
)
